  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Bengel's Gnomen",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Matthew 2:7",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "Αάθρα",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "privily",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") lest anything should transpire. This argues insidious designs on the part of Herod.—",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ἠκρίβωσε",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "enquired diligently",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") even to the smallest particle of time. Hence we perceive the craft of Herod,[88] and the simplicity of the Magi.—",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "φαινομένου",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "appearing",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") The Present Tense. Herod enquired the time at which the star which was now visible, had first become so.[89]",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "[88] So great enmities did that monarch indulge in and foster, although he did not esteem as a fable the doctrine concerning Christ, but was by this time aware of the time and place of His nativity.—",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Vers. Germ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "[89] In the original the passage stands thus—“Præsens tempus, quo conspici cœpta esset stella, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "quœ appareret",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", quaesivit Herodes.” This is evidently a misprint for—“Præsens. Tempus quo conspici cœpta esset stella, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "quœ appareret",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", quaesivit Herodes.”",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "In his German Version Bengel renders the passage “",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "und vernahm von ihnen die Zeit, da der Stern erschienen",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ",” i.e. “",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "and ascertained accurately from them the Time when the Star appeared",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".” In his Harmony he renders it—“",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "und erlernte mit fleis von ihnen wann der Stern erschienen wäre",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ",” i.e. “",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "and learnt with diligence from them, when the star made its appearance",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".”—(I. B.)",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Pulpit Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_sub_title",
        "text": "Verse 7.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " - ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "Then Herod, when he had privily called the Wise Men",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". Secrecy was doubly necessary. He would not publicly commit himself to acknowledging the rights of the new King, and he would give no opportunity for others to warn the Child's parents of the dangerous interest that Herod was taking in him. Duplicity was very characteristic of Herod; cf. his assassination of Aristobulus the high priest (Josephus, 'Ant.,' 15:03. 3), and his alluring his son Antipater home to death (ibid., 17:5. 1). ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "Inquired of them diligently",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "learned of them carefully",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " (Revised Version); \"lerned of hem bisili\" (Wickliffe); ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "ἠκρίβωσεν παρ αὐτῶν",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". The stress is not upon Herod's careful questioning, but on the exact information that he obtained. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "What time the star appeared",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". Although this is not the literal translation, it may, perhaps, represent the sense of the original ( ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "τὸν χρόνον τοῦ φαινομένου ἀστέρος",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") , the participle characterizing the star in its most important relation - its appearance, and the words being treated as a compound expression (cf. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "John 12:9, 12",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). Herod supposed that the birth of the Babe was synchronous with the first appearance of the star. The translation, however, of the Revised Version margin, \"the time of the star that appeared,\" better suits the exact wording ( ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "χρόνον",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", not ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "καιρόν",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ";",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "φαινομένου",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", not ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "φανέντος",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") , the phrase thus including both the first appearance and also the period of continuance (cf. Grotius, \"non initium, sed continuitas\"). But it is difficult to see What Herod would have learned from this latter particular. Some even think that the star was still visible (Plumptre; Weiss, 'Matthew'), but in this case the joy of the Magi in ver. 10 is not satisfactorily explained. Matthew 2:7",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  }
]